H3.text: Who appears on the reverse of the current Bank of England £10 note. Darwin's

A4.text: The current polymer £10 note bears the image of author Jane Austen on the reverse.

A5.text: The final cotton paper note featuring a portrait of naturalist Charles Darwin, first issued in 2000, was withdrawn from circulation on 1 March 2018.
